KANO – Former Vice President, Atiku Abubakar on Thursday paid a condolence visit to the family of the late Kano influential politician, Alhaji Musa Gwadabe. Gwadabe, a former Minister of Labour and Productivity, died Tuesday night in an unnamed health facility in Kano at the of 87. The standard bearer of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in the just conducted February, 25 presidential election was accompanied on the trip by top PDP stalwarts. Atiku Abubakar, while at Gwadabe’s residence expressed his grief about the shocking demise of the Kano-born political politician, as he enjoined the family to take heart. The Wazirin Adamawa during the condolence visit paid a glowing tribute to the deceased political icon describing him as a “patriot and a statesman.” Gwadabe’s family during the interaction with the former Nigerian number two citizen thanked him for identifying with them at the hour of their grief. The former Vice President while in Kano also paid a condolence visit to Alhaji Aminu Dantata who lost his second wife, Hajia Rabi Dantata recently.‒‒:‒‒/‒‒:‒‒ He commiserated with the family, and prayed unto Allah to comfort the family and grant the deceased eternal rest.